On Sat, 28 May 2011, John Kolak wrote:

> Engineers tell us that on average, you should see about 10 psi per
> each 1000 rpm. You should not be running under load at less than 1800
> rpm, so there is a reason for lost pressure. This can be a function of
> choosing oil of too low of viscosity. Otherwise, the other causes of
> pressure loss can be worn engine bearings, worn oil pressure relief
> spring, and worn seats on the oil pressure relief valve.


also depending on how steep the grade was there could have been a pickup 
problem.

I would top off the oil with a good quality oil of at least 10W-40 weight 
since summer is comming and see if there is still a problem.

